Instance Method# getElementValues

DriverKitiOSiPadOSmacOS

```
const IOReportElementValues * getElementValues(int element_index);
```

## [ Parameters ](/documentation/driverkit/ioreporter_ivars/getelementvalues#parameters)

`element_index`
- index of the _element in internal array

## [Return Value](/documentation/driverkit/ioreporter_ivars/getelementvalues#return-value)

A pointer to the element values requested or NULL on failure

## [Discussion](/documentation/driverkit/ioreporter_ivars/getelementvalues#discussion)

Internal method to directly access the values of an element

Locking: Caller must ensure that the reporter (data) lock is held. The returned pointer is only valid until unlockReporter() is called.
